Use `of` to choose the concrete type for a generic declaration.

### One argument

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    Box type A = |
        value A,
    |

    text_box Box of String = Box("hello")
]

### Several arguments

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    Pair type A, B = |
        first A,
        second B,
    |

    item Pair of String, Int = Pair("count", 3)
]

### Concrete aliases

When a type would need nested `of` applications, name an intermediate alias.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    StringIntPair as Pair of String, Int
    value Box of StringIntPair = Box(Pair("count", 3))
]

### Remember

- `of` goes in type position, not in ordinary expressions.
- The number of arguments must match the declaration.
- Different concrete arguments make different types.
